#
# If you are bored, you can take a look at this list of games.
#
# NOTE: This is not a complete list of all free games available for Debian.
# This file contains just a small selection of recommended and popular titles.
# For a full overview, visit: https://blends.debian.org/games/tasks/
#
# Thanks to the fellows from the Debian Games Team
# <debian-devel-games@lists.debian.org> for their work.
#
# You can also take a look at '/root/opt/game-scripts' and learn more with:
# $ game-data-packager --help
# $ play.it --help
#
# Use it if you want install '/root/opt/game-scripts' on your system:
# $ ./init --games
#
# after installation, simply choose any game directory and
# run its 'install.sh' script to set it up.
#
# and you can use meta-packages to install genres in bulk, example:
# $ apt install games-arcade games-rpg
#
# see available genres:
# $ apt-cache depends games-all
# or:
# $ apt-cache search '^games-'
#
